	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Signs and symptoms of breast cancer may include: • a breast lump or thickening that feels different from the surrounding tissue; • change in the size, shape or appearance of a breast; • changes to the skin over the breast, such as dimpling; • a newly inverted nipple; • peeling, scaling, crusting or flaking of the pigmented area of skin surrounding the nipple (areola) or breast skin; and • redness or pitting of the skin over your breast, like the skin of an orange. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  